For any input  [`x`]  and functions  [`f`]  and  [`g`],  this action defines a composite function, which we write as [`f\circle g`]  such that

[``(f\circ g)(x) = f(g(x))``]
 
The domain of the composite function  [`f\circ g`]  is all  [`x`]  such that  [`x`]  is in the domain of  [`g`]  and  [`g(x)`]  is in the domain of  [`f`]. 

